Description.Name: ...there's that knock knock knocking... again...
Description.Details: You sit in your command chair, rubbing your temples to ease the headache and feeling like Phil Connors in that ancient Terran comedy Groundhog Day, "Does the term, 'Groundhog Day' ring any bells for any of you here?" Most of the bridge crew just look at you like you've lost your mind. You wave the comment away with your hand, "Nevermind." Dr Murad has the panel to the Console open again, playing around with the components, "I've tried everything I can Commander, but I think our only option is to replace the parts until the sound goes away." Your head pounding from the random banging resounding out of the Console makes it hard to think clearly, "So we just toss out a possibly good part in the hopes of it fixing the issue? That sounds expensive." Dr Murad stops work on the Console, "After labour from the astechs as well as other bits and pieces, it should not be more than ¢1,000,000 C-Bills." You moan, "Ugh, more expenses. Can we at least sell or reuse the part we replace?" Dr Murad shakes her head, "No Commander. The way these pirates have cobbled this device together basically means you have to literally destroy the part to replace it. So I can either try replacing a part or we can ignore it and hope it goes away on its own."

Description.Details:
You rub your temples for a moment, "Go ahead and change out the Fu Capicitor."

Description.Name: If it's not broke...
Description.Details: Live with the Noise

Description.Name: Live with the Noise
Description.Details:
You rub your temples for a moment, "I just cannot see the logic in blindly replacing a possibly good part.  We've dealt with this random knocking noise so far.  At least it's not happening all the time."

Dr Murad nods and instructs her team of astechs to begin to reassemble the panels of the Console.  As they work, she turns back to you, "I'll let you know when whichver faulty component finally fails and takes the Console fully offline."
